      <item>
          <title>Inktober 2023</title>
          <pubDate>Sat, 23 Sep 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
          <author>Unknown</author>
          <link>https://www.jimmyff.co.uk/gallery/inktober-2023/</link>
          <guid>https://www.jimmyff.co.uk/gallery/inktober-2023/</guid>
          <description xml:base="https://www.jimmyff.co.uk/gallery/inktober-2023/">&lt;p&gt;...Here we go again! It&#x27;s almost #inktober season. This year I&#x27;m trying something a little different by having a single image that I&#x27;ll be adding to each day. I&#x27;ve quite a lot of commitments this year so my time will be pretty limited. I&#x27;m also using it as an excuse to have a try an app called &#x27;Concepts&#x27; - this differs from the art apps I&#x27;ve used before as it uses something called &#x27;Vector Graphics&#x27; which means each stroke and mark is stored as code rather than modifying pixels. I&#x27;ve no idea how this is going to turn out! 😅&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Who else is taking on the challenge this year? 🎨&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;




